@the_shroud: It's a kind of heresy comparing these two movies. One is typical example of very very good idea translated into phantasmagoric script and ruined by silly directing. We all KNOW that Ralph Fiennes, Angela Bassett and  Juliette Lewis are first echelon of actors - but in that movie - they act as - idiots. Who is to blame - we all know too well.

Oh, other one is Blade Runner, a masterpiece, in every possible aspect.

I, unfortunately have BluRay of Strange Days and I can encode 480p or 720p, just let me know which version you want.

@twentyforty: Ha! The first time I saw Strange Days, it made a big impression, but then when I watched it a second time a couple of years ago, I was disappointed. And of course, one would expect Strange Days not to be a masterpiece, given that The Hurt Locker is so mediocre.

I've read enough about the "extra" scenes in the theatrical release of Revenge for it to not be worth my while to watch that, for the time being, anyway.

I'm very fortunate that there is someone who does and uploads excellent HD rips who has similar tastes to my own. :)
